<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-08-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-08-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="139" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 139.</note>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Davis to Mr. Bancroft</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 225.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi><hi rend="italic"> Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-08-23"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 23, 1870.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I inclose herewith, for your information,
                            a copy of a dispatch, No. 253, of the 12th instant, from Mr. Washburne,
                            relative to the measures taken by him for the protection of North
                            Germans in France.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>J. C. B. DAVIS.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>[For this inclosure see, <hi rend="italic">ante,</hi> “France,” Mr.
                                Washburne’s dispatch No. 253, dated August 12, 1870.]</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>